free_txt: THE HIGH-ENERGY GAMMA-RAYS (E GT. 3.5 MEV) WERE
DETECTED WITH A PAIR SPECTROMETER, CONSISTING OF A
HYPER-PURE GERMANIUM DETECTOR, PLACED BETWEEN
TWO NAI(TL) CRYSTALS. THE RESOLUTION OF THE
PAIR SPECTROMETER WAS 2.3 KEV AT 2.3 MEV AND 5.5 KEV
AT 7.6 MEV. THE SPECTROMETER WAS ENERGY CALIBRATED
USING GAMMAS FROM THE AL-27(N,G) REACTION. THE INTEN-
SITY CALIBRATION WAS BASED ON THE ABSOLUTE INTENSITIES
OF A FEW STRON TRANSITIONS IN DY-165.

.BENT-CRYSTAL DIFFRACTION SPECTROMETERS GAMS1 AND

.SECONDARY GAMMA-RAYS BETWEEN 46 AND 750 KEV WERE DE-
TECTED IN STEPS OF 0.9 ARCSECONDS WITH GAMS1. AT THE
SAME TIME GAMS2/3 WAS USED TO SCAN THE ENRGY REGION
FROM 104 TO 2500 KEV IN STEPS OF 0.33 ARCSECONDS. THE
COUNTING TIME WAS 60 SEC./POINT. THE SPECTRUM BETWEEN
112 AND 2000 KEV WAS ALSO REMEASURED IN A SECOND
GAMS2/3 RUN. THE ANGULAR RESOLUTION FOR GAMS1 VARIED
BETWEEN 4 AND 5 ARCSECONDS, CORRESPONDING TO AN ENERGY
RESOLUTION OF 120 EV AT 200 KEV. THE ANGULAR RESOLU-
TION FOR GAMS2/3 VARIED BETWEEN 0.9 AND 1.6 ARCSE-
CONDS, WHICH CORRESPONDS TO AN ENERGY RESOLUTION OF
360 EV AT 800 KEV.
